    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-26T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-26T21:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-26T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 26, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Your 44, February 25, 11 a.m. For McBride. The War Department is sending to
                    Liberia by air within a few days Colonel Leon A. Fox of the Medical Corps and
                    Captain William N. Beard of the Engineers to make appropriate surveys. In the
                    case of Colonel Fox’s mission, it would be helpful if you could arrange in
                    advance for the friendly cooperation of the Liberian Government, as the War
                    Department deems it essential that adequate sanitary and health precautions
                    should be taken before American forces are sent to Liberia.</p>
                <p>Details in regard to the credit plan are promised by the War Department in a day
                    or two, and answers to your questions will be transmitted as soon as possible.
                    Meanwhile preparations are being made for an initial force of Negro troops
                    commanded by white officers, in addition to a detachment of white mechanics and
                    technicians. It is understood that fighter planes will be included in defense
                    equipment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
